Jan 25 2009	Good hotel	A very good hotel in an excellent location. The staff is very helpful and friendly. The breakfast buffet has many things to choose from (fresh fruit, different kinds of bread, cheese, pastry, omelets, sausages etc.). Rooms are in good condition, with TV, washing machine, microwave, oven etc. Good beds. Only the toilet was not perfect, as we did not always get hot water. Despite that, the quality of the toilet was above the toilets of most 3 star level hotels.There was also free parking in the hotel. Note, however, that if you intend to do day trips with a car, Bur Dubai area is in the immediate center of Dubai, meaning very heavy traffic most of the time. You will spend lots of time in the car. This applies to the whole downtown Dubai (especially Deira and Bur Dubai), so all hotels in this area have the same problem. It is also very difficult to find a parking space in this area, so make sure that your hotel has free parking (like Dar al Sondos) if you intend to use a car that is (practically the only option to move from one place to another as there is no real public transportation in Dubai ).The hotel also has free internet in the lobby.I would rate the hotel ****+, not ***. Absolutely recommendable.	
