it Big Brother.The doorman was extremely nice and helpful. The desk staff was not as nice and helpful. You will need to change your money for Dubai, all prices are in their own currency.The weather was a lot cooler than we expected. It seemed to be high 60s low 70s and it rained some days. Not really beach weather. I ended up grabbing a cab and heading back to the airport. Like a previous reviewer, I was supposed to stay 5 nights, but due to this hotel, I didn't stay 1 night. I booked the next flight back to JFK, but word to the wise.....you are not allowed to go through security until 3 hours before your flight, and there are no restaurants or shops or anything on the outside. I slept on a chair for 5 hours.The flight from JFK to Dubai was nice and on a new Emirates plane. We had the row to ourselves and got free kits and all. The flight back was on an older plane and was packed. Not empty seats anywhere. I had a screaming (and kicking) baby behind me for 14 hours. The flight out was only 12 hours.If you are looking for a very budget place to stay and you are a man and you do not want a nice view or a beach, this may be ok. I, personally, was absolutely disgusted, I can't believe Le Meridien put their name on this place. It is one thing if it was a POS place next to all the things you wanted to see....but it was a POS place in the middle of the ghetto.Very very very disappointed in Le Meridien and Starwood for this one.	
