May 7 2008 	Nice affordable hotel - GREAT service offered by friendly people.	We did our research at Trip Advisor and saw many positive reviews of this hotel, so we booked it directly at the hotel's website. Received a great welcome upon our arrival: hot towels, fresh fruit juice and the staff was particularly friendly. Upon check-in, we received a complimentary room upgrade, which was nice. Breakfast was included in the room rate, which helped keep our food expenses lower than we anticipated.FOOD/DRINK - Don't miss the breakfast buffet. It was wonderful. Try to book a room where breakfast is included in your room rate. This will save you $, although we found local food prices to be fairly reasonable. There is also a small grocery store just 1 block away down the particularly busy street. If you have small children, pay close attn. to them as drivers here will not stop for much. NO BAR in this hotel, so alcohol is nowhere in the building. I was told that a few hotels close-by had restaurants w/ bars, but we were not that motivated to find them. 2 bottles of complimentary water provided each day, which was nice to have at the end of each days' activities upon our return. Complimentary hot snacks were also served at the end of the day. Choice was thin, but food was good.SERVICE - The service we received was a SOLID 4 star and more than made up for the 3 star facilities. They understand good service here and are most responsive to any request or call to the front desk. (Upon checkin to the room, we realized the safe was locked. After calling, maintenance arrived in under 5 minutes and fixed it.)LOCATION - Not the best location for Dubai, but taxis are so cheap, one can get anywhere inexpensively. Watch the street here, as it is quite busy. Probably not the best location if you have children, but was more than functional if you don't plan on staying in the hotel's immed. vicinity. (Our small family went to Wild Wadi and Mall of the Emirates over 2 days, so the location was not all that important to us). TAXIS ARE CHEAP, so don't let this location keep you from staying here.POOL - We used it several times. Very functional. Tiles in the pool area were not made for poolside use as they are very slick when wet. Great view from the rooftop/pool area of the Bur Dubai, when it's not too dusty. Fresh towels provided at the pool area. Again, the pool attendant was friendly and we enjoyed our quiet peaceful time relaxing and catching some sun at the pool.ROOMS - Well appointed and comfortable. We got exactly what we paid for. No surprises when we checked in. NO FUNKY HOTEL SMELL, as is often the case in so many places. The hotel's website gave us advanced notice that there was construction going on beside our hotel - We really appreciated the warning, but happy to report that they basically worked during normal work hours, so it did not inconvenience us at all. As is the case in much of Dubai, construction work is going on practically everywhere, so do not be surpised if you encounter construction noise regardless of your hotel choice in Dubai. Comfy bed, nice bathroom, but not huge. Everything was functional. No place to plug in hot water pot for coffee/tea, but this was solved with one quick call to maintenance, who promptly responded w/ in 5 minutes with a converter.OVERALL - The people make all the difference at the Dar al Sondos Hotel Apartments. As an american expat traveling w/ my wife and 4 yr. old son, this hotel was just fine for our needs. Daytime activities took us out of the hotel most of the day, and upon our return, it was more than comfortable and quite affordable. Wouldn't call it a &quot;great deal for the money&quot;, but would say that we were generally happy with our experience based on the rate that we paid. I would recommend this hotel to western expats venturing to Dubai for their first trip, esp. if you don't want to spend a lot of $ to just get out and explore this exciting/vibrant city for a few days.	
