Nov 30 2007 	An Excellent Option for Beating the High Prices of Dubai	If visiting Dubai during the high season or a big event, the hotel prices are outrageous. In an effort to lower the costs, my wife and I stayed at Dar Al Sondos by Le Meridian, an apartment hotel. The room was booked on the Starwood website. The hotel is just off the river in Burj Dubai on a quiet street with small businesses. The room was an efficiency apartment with a bath, kitchen (with washer), sitting area and two twin beds. Although a small hotel, it is a full-service with a restaurant, internet station for a fee and tour desk. The upper floors are executive rooms with access to a lounge on the top floor, which also has the pool and fitness center.I was impressed with the quality of the hotel, service and location. Except for the tile floors, this equates to an upscale motel in the States. Close to the hotel is a 7/11 type store, an inexpensive chicken/pizza eatery, several laundries and a large supermarket. While not inexpensive, the Dar Al Sondos provides an option for budget travelers and businessmen seeking relief from the high prices of Dubai.	
