Jan 31 2006	Good value for money	We stayed here back in september 2005. It was fantastic value for money.The hotel is located near the electronics souk area. It isn't too far from BurJuman shopping centre, although it can seem it in 40 degree heat. Taxis are readily available and are really cheap. The kitchen is well equipped and the washing machine is very helpful. Our room was very cleaned and the sheets/towels changed daily. Room service is also very good and very good value.There are supermarkets and shops nearby so buying food and supplies isn't a problem.The hotel is about 15-20 minutes to the nearest abra station (there is also a very large Carrefour supermarket there).Take an abra across the creek to the gold souk.. much better than sitting in a taxi in traffic.There is building going on beside the hotel, but, in Dubai, where isn't there building happening!! Even the 5star hotels on the beach are beside building sites. A major plus with the hotel being part of the meridian group is that you get to use the private beaches at the sister hotels. We used the Le Royal Meridian Beach Resort &amp; Spa.. it was fantastic.. You must be staying at one of the other meridan hotels to use their facilities. In the lobby of the hotel, Net Tours have a representative to organise some activities while you are in Dubai. We booked the Dhow dinner cruise with them. The driver was 45mins late (even though he is supposed to ring the hotel and advise if he is stuck in traffic or delayed). We were not impressed with them. The cruise was fine, apart from not having air conditioning which wasn't too nice. We then booked the desert safari with Arabian Adventures, who in contrast couldn't do enough to help. Our driver was very friendly and knowledgeable. There is a fantasic little indian/chinese (yes it does both) across the road from the hotel. It is extremely well priced and the food is wonderful.	
Jan 24 2006	Great facilities and value for money	On a recent trip to UK from Australia my 15 year old son and I stopped over in Dubai in both directions. We had a great time and would definitely return.On the outward journey we stayed at Le Merdien Dar al Sondos hotel. The hotel provided free pick up from the airport and they were waiting for us once we cleared Customs. The hotel is situated in a quiet street in Bur Dubai about 20 minutes from the airport. It does not look very impressive from the outside but we found it more than met our needs. We wanted to stay somewhere reasonably priced which is quite hard to do in Dubai. The package on their website included breakfast and it was $A150 a night. Our room was large and clean with a little balcony. The best asset was a small kitchen which also had a washing machine. This was great as we had been to Bangkok before Dubai and needed to do our laundry. The hotel provided at clothes airer on request and everything dried on the balcony. The breakfast provided was good and well presented. The pool area was well kept, but the tiles were treacherously slippery underfoot, a great deal of care was needed with wet feet. The hotel provides a daily shuttle to their sister beach property. There were local supermarkets in the street as well as a bakery, shawerma shop and a good Indian restaurant. We did not find the hotel noisy except for the morning call to prayer from nearby mosque. All part of the atmosphere of being in UAE.We would certainly stay here again	
