Mar 21 2005	7 day city break cheap and cheerful	Booked the Dar Al Sondos via KLM web site, as frequent visitors to Dubai on this occasion we were looking for a cheap and cheerful Studio Apartment. The Dar Al Sondos pretty much fitted the bill (note no bar so pick up your drinks at the duty free on arrivals at the airport, but it does have a coffee shop). 3 Star Hotel Apartments are plentiful in Dubai if you know your way around, and this one is in a good location for walking to Bur Dubai (Fort and Museum, Heritage Village, Creek), Bur Jurman Shopping Mall, etc. Hotel has a few little touches that the le Merdien brings, nice roof top pool (only about 18 loungers), gym, very friendly staff, but cant get overly excited about the breakfast which in fairness was all there, juices, cereals, breads, rolls, cold cuts, cheeses, hot buffet scrambled eggs..etc. Sounds fine but not quite making the standard. The rooms are very clean and serviced daily, they are also fitted with 2 ring electric hob, micro wave oven, fridge, washing machine. There is also a shuttle bus to the beach (Sister Hotel) and there is a Tour Agent in the lobby. Check out time is 12:00 but you can shower and freshen up in the gym/sauna (up to 22:00) if you have a late flight.We hired a car to exploring during the day and walked around at night. In summary very good for what it is, a 3 star hotel apartment.	
